    <h2 id=3D"understanding">Understanding Frame Sizes</h2>
    <p>Frame sizes are labeled by the size of the print or glass they hold,=
 not the outside frame. For example, an =E2=80=9C8=C3=9710 frame=E2=80=9D f=
its an 8=C3=9710 inch photo (the outer frame will be larger depending on st=
yle). The most common sizes are 4=C3=976, 5=C3=977, and 8=C3=9710 for small=
 to medium photos, with larger formats like 16=C3=9720 and 24=C3=9736 used =
for statement wall art.</p>

    <h2 id=3D"ranges">Small, Medium, Large &amp; Extra=E2=80=91Large Frames=
</h2>
    <h3>Small (4=C3=976, 5=C3=977)</h3>
    <p>Great for desks, shelves, and tight wall spaces. Perfect for portrai=
ts, travel photos, and small gifts.</p>
    <h3>Medium (8=C3=9710, 11=C3=9714, 12=C3=9716)</h3>
    <p>Ideal for family portraits, wedding photos, and certificates. Works =
on tabletops or walls.</p>
    <h3>Large (16=C3=9720, 18=C3=9724, 20=C3=9730)</h3>
    <p>Best for big portraits, art prints, and professional photography. De=
signed for wall display.</p>
    <h3>Extra=E2=80=91Large (24=C3=9736, 30=C3=9740)</h3>
    <p>For posters, panoramic prints, and oversized art. Always wall=E2=80=
=91mounted and a strong focal point.</p>

    <h2 id=3D"choosing">How to Choose the Right Frame Size</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
<strong>Photo resolution:</strong> Bigger prints need higher resolution for=
 sharp results.</li>
      <li>
<strong>Display space:</strong> Balance frame size with your wall or shelf =
area.</li>
      <li>
<strong>Matting:</strong> Mats elevate presentation but require the next fr=
ame size up.</li>
      <li>
<strong>Number of subjects:</strong> Group photos usually look better large=
r.</li>
      <li>
<strong>Style:</strong> Slim frames keep things minimal; thicker frames add=
 presence.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id=3D"matting">Matting &amp; Frame Size</h2>
    <p>No mat? Match frame to print size. Using a mat? Size up the frame. C=
ommon pairings:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>5=C3=977 photo =E2=86=92 8=C3=9710 frame (with mat)</li>
      <li>8=C3=9710 photo =E2=86=92 11=C3=9714 frame (with mat)</li>
      <li>11=C3=9714 photo =E2=86=92 16=C3=9720 frame (with mat)</li>
      <li>16=C3=9720 photo =E2=86=92 20=C3=9724 frame (with mat)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For custom mat widths or non=E2=80=91standard prints, use the calcul=
ator at the top to get precise outer dimensions and a scaled preview.</p>
